   "source": [
    "First some basic questions to answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "    1.) Who were the passengers on the Titanic? (Ages,Gender,Class,..etc)\n",
    "\n",
    "    2.) What deck were the passengers on and how does that relate to their class?\n",
    "\n",
    "    3.) Where did the passengers come from?\n",
    "\n",
    "    4.) Who was alone and who was with family?\n",
    "\n",
    "Then we'll dig deeper, with a broader question:\n",
    "\n",
    "    5.) What factors helped someone survive the sinking?"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "## Who were the passengers on the Titanic?"

   "source": [
    "# See how many men and women are in each Pclass, where the Pclass is the independent variable.\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.catplot(x='Pclass',data=titanic_df,kind='count',hue='Sex')"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 88,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Now we want to see the ratio of men to women to children.\n",
    "# For this, let's assume anybody under the age of 21 is a child.\n",
    "# Let's create a function that alters the considers the person a child if they are under 21.\n",
    "\n",
    "def man_women_child(passenger):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    age, sex = passenger\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if age<21:\n",
    "        return 'child'\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return sex"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 89,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Make a new column that uses the apply function to use the newly created function to determine whether a person\n",
    "# is a man, women, or a child.\n",
    "\n",
    "titanic_df['person'] = titanic_df[['Age','Sex']].apply(man_women_child,axis=1)"
   ]

    "# What was the average Fare price for men and women?\n",
    "\n",
    "men_fare_price = []\n",
    "women_fare_price = []\n",
    "\n",
    "def men_and_women_Fare_price(passenger):\n",
    "    sex, price = passenger\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if sex == 'male':\n",
    "        return men_fare_price.append(price)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return women_fare_price.append(price)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# Create a counting plot that shows how many people \n",

   "source": [
    "# Now let's consider how many people embarked from each city,\n",
    "# while taking into consideration the class of each passenger as well:\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.catplot(x='Embarked',data=titanic_df,kind='count',hue='Pclass',order=list('CQS'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As we can see, City Q had a lot of 3rd class individuals board and City C had a considerable amount of 1st class passengers."
   ]
  },
  {
